The paper deals with interference mitigation techniques in cellular networks, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science. The most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), as the paper originates from information-theoretic principles and analyzes the sum-rate throughput using the asymptotic eigenvalue distribution of channel covariance matrices. The second likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), as the paper deals with clustered Base Stations and cochannel interference allowance, which are relevant to network architecture and design. The third likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), as the paper investigates cooperation among Base Stations and the impact of intercluster interference on network performance. The fourth likely category is cs.MM (Multimedia), as the paper considers the throughput gains of multicell joint processing in cellular networks, which is relevant to multimedia applications. The fifth likely category is cs.COM (Computers and Society), as the paper discusses the practical implementation of interference alignment and resource division multiple access in cellular networks, which has implications for the social and economic aspects of network deployment.
